         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">16/10/87. ¶  ¶ The realisation of the proposed exploring in Central Australia, will largely depend, dear Sir Samuel, on assurances of the S.A. &amp; WA. Government, to secure at some fair estimate the map...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.10.16</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Samuel Davenport</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Collection of the Royal Geographical Society of Australasia (South Australia Branch) Inc., State Library of South Australia, Adelaide.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation: 'recd 22 Octr'.</p>
               </note>16/10/87.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The realisation of the proposed exploring in Central Australia, will largely depend, dear Sir Samuel, on assurances of the S.A. &amp; WA. Government, to secure at some fair estimate the map &amp; report of the Expedition; and I hope your branch of the R.GS.A<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Royal Geographical Society of Australasia.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>will be successful in a double appeal so far. Mr Giles<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ernest Giles.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has changed his plan of proceeding for a few months tour in business-interests to the Kimberley-District,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>WA.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by taking the eastern route; so you will not see him on his way Though we are sorry for this delay his services should be secured, — if possible —, as he goes without salary —, and has such courage and experience. During the race-time, I trust, my colleagues of the geographic Council here will help me further, to obtain contributions for the expedition-fund though I have hardly ever leisure to be present at races.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>annual<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Spring<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>horse-racing carnival,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>including the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Melbourne Cup<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>run each year on the first Tuesday in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>November.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is very friendly of you, to invite me to the grand Adelaide-Expedition,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. Exhibition; the Jubilee International Exhibition, Adelaide, 1887.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>which is so splendidly carried through; but I am passing just for this season's work still the "dichotomous Key to the system of Victorian plants" through the press;<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B88.11.02.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and if I went away for a week, it would throw back the just now overpowering departmental work for a whole month. Indeed the local Parliament demands a new edition of my volume on select plants now also, the last (the sixth in the English language) having been sold within 7 month of its issue from the Gov. Printing office here.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The new edition was published in late 1888 (B88.12.01), the previous edition having appeared in 1885 (85.12.03).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>So I may not even be able, to have the pleasure of a journey to Adelaide in midsummer, the only time, when it would be comparatively safe to travel for me.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me hope that next year Lady Davenport and yourself will be here for the Melbourne Exhibition,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn8" n="9">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Centennial International Exhibition, Melbourne, 1888.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>so that I also may often have the pleasure of meeting her Ladyship and yourself</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful remembrance</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>always your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The Exhibition-jurors there have been most generous to me.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn9" n="10">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>M was awarded a number of medals and certificates<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for his contributions to the Adelaide Exhibition;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>see<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the undated series, Adelaide<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Jubilee International Exhibition to M, in this edition as 87-12-00n<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to 87-12-00s.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>jury process allowed for appeals and the process was not completed until December, hence the attribution of the certificates to December.</p>
                     <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
